                     # Nachos Kernel – Threading and User Program Support

## Overview
Implemented core threading and synchronization primitives and extended the Nachos kernel to support user processes and executable loading.

## Implemented Components

### Threading Subsystem
- Implemented preemptive KThread scheduling
- Built Lock and Condition primitives with proper sleep/wakeup semantics
- Implemented ready queue management using a custom doubly linked list
- Resolved race conditions in thread context switching

### User Programs
- Implemented executable (.coff) loading
- Built address space initialization
- Implemented basic system call handling
- Modified UserKernel and UserProcess to support process creation and termination

### Modified Files:
- threads/KThread.java
- threads/Lock.java
- threads/Condition.java
- threads/DLLList.java
- userprog/UserKernel.java
- userprog/UserProcess.java
- test/*.c

## How To Run & Contribute
-  From the config/ directory:
``` cd config
	make 
```
- Then run ``` java nachos.machine.Machine -d ac -x ../test/writeTest.coff ``` (still from config/)

